<br>
From a cleric- If the cleric is level 60, I ask for Aegonism (Aego). If you see that the cleric is a bit bussy or if we don't have a level 60, ask for symbol &amp; armor from a lower level one. DO NOT ask for Aego if you have Protection of the Glades (PotG)on. Also if there is no druid or shammy around they can give you a few resist buffs.<br>
<br>
From a shammy- Also depends on the level. If there is a level 60 shammy I ask for Focus of Spirit (Focus) &amp; Ritorous Health &amp; and Delirious Nimble. If the shammy is not 60, ask for Strength and Stamina buffs. Shamans also have some resist buff. If Grubb is on and we need PR, tell your group to take off poison resist buff EXCEPT Dead Man Floating). And have the group leader ask for the buff. They can also haste if there is no enchanter. If you are asked to get shrinked. Have a shaman join your group for a few seconds and he/she will shrink you.<br>
<br>
From a ranger- Get Call of Earth and Strength of Nature. Do not ask for Strength of Nature if you have Divine Strength or BMB (Both Paladin Buffs). And if the ranger is level 60 tell the group leader to ask for Call of the Predator.<br>
<br>
From a Paladin- If the paladin is below level 60 you can ask for Divine Glory (100hp buff). If 60, ask for Divine Strength. If the paladin is uber like Tuxtrin, tell your group leader to ask for BMB.<br>
<br>
From an Enchanter- If the enchanter is below 54, get clarity. If the enchanter is above 54, get Clarity 2. Ifthe enchanter is uber like Sirtiely or Megalo, have group leader ask for Clarity 3. Ask any enchanter for haste, the higher the level of the enchanter the better the haste. If we have an enchanter with epic, ask him. Also in rare cases you may be asked to get Rune, ask an enhanter for that. Enchanters can also give Group Magic Resist. Ask your group leader for it.<br>
<br>
From a Necromancer- Not much. Dead Man Floating and Feeding mana is all I ever ask very rarely.<br>
<br>
From a mage- Summon Mod Rods. If the mage has Mod Rod 2 use that. They can also summon nice resist gear. Our mages have the good habit of calling out what they are summoning and where they are dropping it. I also ask for Dispell Staffs if I am bait for Trakanon. Iguess they could also damage shield you if you want.<br>
<br>
From a druid- This is the one I am a bit lost on because I don't ask for many druid buffs. The big ones are Circle of Summer/Winter. If the druid has Circle of Seasons you can ask for that. Note that circles buffs are group effect for have the group leader ask for them Do not ask for Circle of Summer/Winter if you or someone in your group has Seasons. They can regen and put damage shields on you. Protection of the Glades is a buff lots of casters seem to like as well as Skin like Nature. But I never ask for those so /shrug. They can also symbol.<br>
<br>
Bards- Bards know what to sing, let them do their thing.<br>
<br>
Beastlord- Who know heh.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps some people.<br>
